{
  "texts": [
    "To minimize the randomness introduced in the generation, we use greedy decoding with the decoding temperature set to 0, a common practice in research involving LLMs to ensure reproducible results (Wang et al., 2023).",
    "We set the maximum response length to 256 tokens.",
    "In total, the models generated 9,641 unique responses, including emotions and related words, emojis, and refusals.",
    "To identify the emotions linked to each gendered persona, we remove any model responses with more than one word foot_3 and accommodate grammatical variations (e.g., angry to anger, sad to sadness, etc.).",
    "After filtering those responses, our dataset consists of 212,936 emotion attribution completions, with 471 unique emotionrelated words."
  ]
}